<HEAD>Locusts Blown In From Sahara Mate, Leave A Family</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two locusts that were blown to Britain from the
Sahara Desert in west Africa during a sandstorm last October mated
in a school laboratory in southwest England, a newspaper said Sunday.
   The Sunday Telegraph said the inch-long locusts bred at the
Plymstock Comprehensive School in Plymouth when the school was
closed over Christmas and have since died, leaving a healthy family
of 27.
