<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Nigeria-Bones     02-05 0093</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Nigeria-Bones,0095</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Arrest Sellers Of Human Parts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested three people for trading in
human skulls and other body parts in a local market, the Sunday
Concord reported.
   The newspaper said police recovered five human skulls, including
jaw bones, and several leg, hand and arm bones. The arrests were
made Saturday after police were tipped about the sales.
   One of those arrested told police that most of the body parts
were bought from cemetary attendants.
   Human skulls and bones have been used in some West Africa rituals.
