<DOCNO> AP890205-0011 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-02-05-89 1134EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-Belgium-ChessMoves     02-05 0266</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Belgium-Chess Moves,0331</SECOND>
<HEAD>Moves From Match Between Timman and Portisch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANTWERP, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Following are the moves from the fourth
game of the World Chess Championship Candidates quarterfinal between
Dutch grandmaster Jan Timman and Hungary's Lajos Portisch.
   The contest was adjourned after six hours of play on Saturday and
declared a draw on Sunday without being resumed.
   White: Timman
   Black: Portisch
   Opening: Ruy Lopez
   1. e4 e5
   2. Nf3 Nc6
   3. Bb5 a6
   4. Ba4 Nf6
   5. 0-0 Be7
   6. Re1 b5
   7. Bb3 d6
   8. c3 0-0
   9. h3 Bb7
   10. d4 Re8
   11. Ng5 Rf8
   12. Nf3 Re8
   13. Nbd2 Bf8
   14. a3 h6
   15. Bc2 Nb8
