<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Swiss-Drought     02-05 0101</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Swiss-Drought,0103</SECOND>
<HEAD>Water Rationing Weighed In South Switzerland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOCARNO, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Town officials in southernmost
Switzerland considered rationing drinking water Sunday as
meteorologists reported a record 62-day dry spell in the region.
   A meteorologist predicted no major weather changes over the next
10 days for the southern tip of Ticino state, which borders Italy.
   The dry spell is the longest on record. Records have been kept
125 years, the meteorologist said.
   Several towns prohibited the use of automatic car washes last
week. Fires sparked by the drought have destroyed nearly 100 acres
of forest and brush in the area.
</TEXT>
